      • getPresentationOrExtentOrPersistentID

        public java.util.List<java.lang.Object> getPresentationOrExtentOrPersistentID()
        Gets the value of the presentationOrExtentOrPersistentID property.

        This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the presentationOrExtentOrPersistentID property.

        For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

            getPresentationOrExtentOrPersistentID().add(newItem);

        Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list JAXBElement<MassDouble> JAXBElement<Plane> JAXBElement<Shape> JAXBElement<CompositeCurve> JAXBElement<BsplineSurface> GenericAttributes JAXBElement<TrimmedCurve> Position ConnectionPoints JAXBElement<String> JAXBElement<Circle> JAXBElement<String> Label JAXBElement<Association> JAXBElement<String> JAXBElement<Ellipse> Text JAXBElement<CurveBoundedSurface> JAXBElement<Surface> JAXBElement<Line> History JAXBElement<String> Presentation JAXBElement<String> JAXBElement<Curve> JAXBElement<String> Extent JAXBElement<PolyLine> JAXBElement<BsplineCurve> Identifier JAXBElement<PersistentID> JAXBElement<String> Scale
